# Cline / AI Assistant Rules — Portfolio

## Project Context

Personal portfolio for Cillian Ó Murchú. React 18 + TypeScript + Vite.
Full context: README.md, docs/ARCHITECTURE.md, docs/STYLE_GUIDE.md, docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md

## Structure Rules

- Route screens → `src/pages/`
- Feature with 2+ related files → `src/components/<feature>/` folder (co-locate hook, util, type, component)
- General hooks → `src/hooks/`
- General utils → `src/utils/`
- Context providers → `src/context/`
- Static data → `src/data/`
- CSS → `src/styles/theme.css` (no new CSS files)

## Coding Rules

- TypeScript strict. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore`.
- No `console.log` in production code.
- Keep components under 150 lines. Extract sub-components into same folder.
- Use `utils/animations.ts` scroll variants — do not define local Framer Motion variants.
- Use `theme.css` utility classes before writing inline styles.
- No new dependencies without clear justification.
- After structural changes, run `npm run build` to verify.

## Import Paths

Relative imports only. No aliases.

```
pages/          → ../components, ../hooks, ../utils, ../data, ../context
components/xyz/ → ../../hooks, ../../utils, ../../context
components/sphere/ → ./[sibling]  (sphere is self-contained)
components/name/   → ./[sibling]  (name is self-contained)
```

## Do Not

- Install Three.js (sphere is canvas-based, not Three.js)
- Add sphere/name utils to src/utils/ — they belong in their feature folder
- Define animation variants locally — add to utils/animations.ts scrollVariants
- Use wildcard versions in package.json
- Build on useAuth or useElementCenter — both are dead code

## Known Bugs

- HeroTitle buttons have no onClick — selectedItem in HomeScreen never changes
- Navbar uses `border-bottom-neon`, theme.css defines `border-neon-bottom` (mismatch)
- Contact form does nothing — input/button are UI-only placeholders

See docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md for full list.
